te, and found that V1251 Cyg and RZ Leo have\nlonger supercycles than those of other WZ Sge-type dwarf novae. This result\nindicates that these long-period objects including ASASSN-16eg have a low\nmass-transfer rate in comparison to other WZ Sge-type dwarf novae.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Aug 2017 10:23:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 22 Sep 2017 11:15:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-25"}
